<subSubSection id="C33C09E7FFE0FFB967206F95FBB3BE0E" pageId="11" pageNumber="114" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B995A6CFFE0FFB967206F95FB1DBE41" blockId="11.[831,1437,1705,1824]" pageId="11" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis id="B952867EFFE0FFB967206F95FC02BFA1" bold="true" box="[831,944,1705,1728]" pageId="11" pageNumber="114">Remarks:</emphasis>
The species was based on a single specimen collected at Limbin, 
<collectingRegion id="49E2948EFFE0FFB960546FF5FB50BF81" box="[1099,1250,1737,1760]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="New Ireland" pageId="11" pageNumber="114">New Ireland</collectingRegion>
, and remained unrecorded since. The shape of its flagellum is diagnostic (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB7279DFFE0FFB967FA6E35FBECBE41" author="Lobl I." box="[997,1118,1801,1824]" pageId="11" pageNumber="114" pagination="221 - 224" refId="ref11181" refString="Lobl I. 1980. Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Scaphidiidae Neuirlands. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen entomologischen Gesellschaft 53: 221 - 224." type="journal article" year="1980">Löbl, 1980</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 3).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B995A6CFFE0FFB967206E04FBB3BE0E" blockId="11.[831,1437,1848,1903]" pageId="11" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis id="B952867EFFE0FFB967206E04FC13BE2E" bold="true" box="[831,929,1848,1871]" pageId="11" pageNumber="114">Habitat:</emphasis>
Secondary forests on limestone, very humid soil and leaf litter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
